3D ANATOMY MODELS
The 3D anatomy content is derived from Z-Anatomy, the libre 3D atlas of anatomy,
by Gauthier Kervyn and Marcin Zielinski -- licensed CC BY-SA 4.0.
  https://www.z-anatomy.com/   |   https://github.com/Z-Anatomy

Z-Anatomy is itself derived from BodyParts3D, (c) The Database Center for Life
Science (DBCLS) -- licensed CC BY-SA 2.1 Japan.
  https://dbarchive.biosciencedbc.jp/en/bodyparts3d/

Attribution chain:
  BodyParts3D (DBCLS, CC BY-SA 2.1 JP)
    -> Z-Anatomy (Kervyn & Zielinski, CC BY-SA 4.0)
      -> Anatomed

Changes made (indicated per CC BY-SA 4.0 section 3(a)(1)(B)): the Z-Anatomy source
was modified for this project. Region subsets are extracted and shown ("region
isolation"; no whole body system is rendered); the models were re-exported to
glTF/GLB and meshopt-compressed for streaming; vessels and nerves were re-exported
from the Z-Anatomy Startup.blend to preserve their thin curve geometry; and a
validated catalogue (parts-catalog.json) plus a nearest-neighbour dataset
(parts-neighbors.json) were generated from the models.

